    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-02T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="693"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-02T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1916, 3 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4117. Your 5223, November 27. Department willing to accept Foreign Office’s
                    explanation as to <persName corresp="#p_SJHA1"
                        >Stabler</persName>-<persName>Cadogan</persName> agreement and will not
                    invoke it with reference to future shipments provided Foreign Office willing to
                    allow uninterrupted shipment of <persName>DeRekowski</persName> and Michigan
                    Sugar Company consignments, which have been shipped from Germany and Austria and
                    paid for on the basis of assurances <hi rend="italic">bona fide</hi> given them
                    by this Department that Great Britain has indicated that she would allow
                    uninterrupted shipment of such consignments; hence good faith of Government of
                    United States is involved as firms have acted and paid for seed on basis
                    assurances of Department. So inform Foreign Office and urge importance
                    settlement these two shipments as promptly as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
